    <main>
        <div class="teachers">
            <!-- Hero Section -->
            <section class="homePageSection1">
                <h1 style="text-align: center;"> "Our Story"
                </h1>
                <p style="padding-inline: 30px">Ross Daly and Angela Cox-Daly are professional teachers and performing
                    musicians, both with over 40 years
                    of
                    experience, who share their passion for music while making learning fun! Together, they co-founded
                    Daly
                    Music Academy in 1987. They were also itinerant string teachers for the Scarborough and Etobicoke
                    Boards
                    of
                    Education from 1987-1988. Over the years, they have been teachers at various music camps and
                    adjudicators at
                    several music festival competitions.
                    "We both love teaching and being an integral part of our students' musical growth. We inspire our
                    students
                    to reach their highest potential by offering quality private lessons, recital performance
                    opportunities,
                    master classes, audition preparation, music festival participation (e.g. Kiwanis, Rotary) and Royal
                    Conservatory of Music (RCM) examination preparation.
                    Music is enriching and FUN!"
                </p>
            </section>

            <!-- Grid Section after Hero Section to have images with clip path and text -->
            <section class="homePageSection2-parent">
                <!--  child elements of grid section -->
                <div class="homePageSection2-child">
                    <h1>
                        Angela Cox Daly
                    </h1>
                    <p class="sideText">
                        Angela has over 40 years of teaching experience and is passionate to share her expertise and
                        gift of
                        music
                        with students of all ages! <br /><br />
                        Angela was on scholarship on both violin and piano at the Royal Conservatory of Music (Toronto)
                        in
                        the
                        Course for Gifted Students for seven years and was a recipient of over one hundred awards and
                        scholarships
                        in both piano and violin prior to graduating from the University of Toronto with a Bachelor of
                        Music
                        in
                        Performance degree (MusBacPerf) in 1987. <br /><br />
                        Angela was a member of the Kitchener Waterloo Symphony Orchestra (KWSO) for 32 years, performing
                        as
                        Second
                        Associate Concertmaster until 2003. After a playing related injury and almost two years off,
                        Angela
                        gratefully returned as a section first violinist. She is an active chamber music performer in
                        Canada
                        and the
                        United States and has appeared as soloist with various chamber and symphony orchestras including
                        the
                        Kitchener Waterloo Symphony, Kitchener Waterloo Community Orchestra, Scarborough Philharmonic
                        and
                        the North
                        York Symphony, and the Keene Chamber Orchestra (Keene, NH, USA) <br /><br />
                        Angela enjoys a versatile career including conducting the KWS Youth Strings, teaching violin and
                        piano
                        privately and at schools, coaching string ensembles, adjudicating numerous music festivals &
                        competitions in
                        Ontario, and instructing and performing at summer music festivals. She was on faculty at Wilfrid
                        Laurier
                        University (Waterloo, ON) as a violin instructor, 1990, 1991. <br /><br />
                        Angela and Ross have three children who have been members of all levels of the wonderful
                        Kitchener-Waterloo
                        Youth Orchestra programme.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="homePageSection2-child">
                    <div class="profile-card">
                        <div class="img">
                            <img src="../images/angela-cox-daly.jpg">
                        </div>
                        <div class="caption">
                            <p>Violin | Piano</p>
                            <p>Music Director and Teacher</p>
