                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Another grid Section after Hero Section to have images with clip path and text -->
            <section class="homePageSection3-parent">
                <!--  child elements of grid section -->
                <div class="homePageSection3-child">
                    <div class="profile-card">
                        <div class="img">
                            <img src="/images/Ross-Daly.jpg">
                        </div>
                        <div class="caption">
                            <p>Violin | Viola | Fiddle | Piano | Bass | Theory | Music Arranging</p>
                            <p>Music Director and Teacher</p>
                            <div class="social-links">
                                <a href="#"><i class="fab fa-facebook"></i></a>
                                <a href="#"><i class="fab fa-instagram"></i></a>
                                <a href="#"><i class="fab fa-twitter"></i></a>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="homePageSection3-child">
                    <h1>
                        Ross Daly
                    </h1>
                    <p class="sideText">
                        Ross graduated from the University of Toronto with a Bachelor of Music in Performance degree
                        (MusBacPerf) in
                        1987. He has been a professional musician for 35 years and has performed around the globe
                        including
                        Canada
                        (coast-to-coast), USA, Mexico, the Dominican Republic & Abu Dhabi. His main instruments are
                        violin
                        and viola
                        (acoustic & electric), piano/keyboard and electric bass. He is also noted as a music arranger,
                        composer,
                        conductor and music festival adjudicator. Ross performs many styles of music - including
                        classical,
                        rock,
                        pop, blues, jazz, Celtic, Latin, Oktoberfest, new age, original, seasonal, etc. - in several
                        different
                        ensembles, bands and tribute stage shows.<br /><br />
                        Ross was the conductor and program director of the Mannheim Youth Strings; has conducted
                        rehearsals
                        and
                        sectional sessions with the Kitchener Waterloo Symphony Youth Strings; and currently directs and
                        conducts
                        the Classical Rock Orchestra Camp.<br /><br />
                        Ross is also the President of Daly Live Music & Entertainment (DLME), Ovation Symphonic
                        Productions
                        (OSP),
                        and is the Vice President of the Central Ontario Musicians' Association (Canadian Federation of
                        Musicians).<br /><br />
                        Ross is also a certified Personal Trainer Specialist. He offers unique fitness training programs
                        which are
                        specifically designed to increase your strength, endurance, and flexibility, and will assist in
                        injury
                        prevention - helping you perform at your optimum! The nutrition component will also help you
                        meet or
                        exceed
                        your weight loss goals! For more information see Daly Fitness. <br>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>
        </div>
